      "role": "user",
      "content": "ok that makes more sense. so if the p-value was like 0.06 instead of 0.04, would that change how we look at the uncertainty in the results? like is there a way to quantify how much \"noise\" or randomness is interfering with the data?",
      "source": "evaluator"
